column14: 'Hot Dots' - May/June 2001",,"Cindy's full name is Cynthia Ann Crawford. - Her rise to fame started after she entered the 1982 Elite Look of the Year contest, although she didn't win. - She had been studying Chemical Engineering at Northwestern University. - Cindy is famous for her trademark mole above her top lip, though it was edited out of the picture used for her first Vogue cover. - She has featured in Playboy (1988 and 1998) and the Peter Lindbergh's book ""10 Women"". - She appeared in the 1994 Pirelli Calendar. - In 1992-1993, she was listed as one of People magazine's '50 Most Beautiful People'. - For five years she hosted the MTV 'House of Style', and also her own show 'Sex with Cindy Crawford'. - She starred in the film ""Fair Game"" with William Baldwin (her younger sister, Danielle, was a production assistant on the film) and appeared in the Bon Jovi music video ""Please Come Home for Christmas"" and also in George Michael's video 'Freedom'. - She had a song entitled ""Cindy C."" dedicated to her by Prince. - Cindy's own releases include several calendars, two exercise videos entitled ""Shape Your Body"" and ""The Next Challenge"", a book, ""Cindy Crawford's Basic Face: A Makeup Wookbook"" and her own line of childrens sneakers called Cindys. - Cindy heads her own company - 'Crawdaddy Inc.'. - Her Official Website is: www.cindy.com",B,FALSE,FALSE,NA,http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cindy_Crawford,http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/Cindy_Crawford

column26: 'Interview' - October 2010",Boxing,"Naomi was discovered by Beth Boldt of Elite in Covent Garden when she was 15 years old and still studying at the Italia Conti Stage School. - She was the first black model to appear on the cover of French Vogue, and was part of the supermodel trinity along with Linda Evangelista and Christy Turlington. - As well as writing her own book - a novel entitled \'Swan\', she was featured in Peter Lindbergh\'s book \'10 Women\', Madonna\'s book \'Sex\'. - She has appeared in the films \'Quest for Fire\', \'Cool as Ice\', \'Miami Rhapsody\' and \'Girl 6\'. She has also had short parts in \'The Cosby Show\' and \'Absolutely Fabulous\' and featured in music videos for George Michael (\'Freedom\'), Aretha Franklin, Michael Jackson (\'The Closet\'), Macy Gray (\'Sexual Revolution\'), Madonna (\'Erotica\') and Jay-Z (\'Change Clothes\'). - She has recorded her own CD with Epic records called \'Babywoman\' and also a single with Toshi Kubota called \'La-La-La Love Song\'. - Along with Claudia Schiffer and Karen Mulder, Naomi has a toy doll made in her likeness by the toy manufacturer Hasbro. - She co-owns the Fashion Caf_ restaurant chain with Claudia Schiffer and Elle MacPherson, and is featured in Madame Tussard\'s wax museum. - Naomi was featured in a Bob Marley music video when she was 5 years old. - She appeared in the 1987 & 1995 Pirelli Calendar. - She appeared in the 1997 & 2002 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit.",B,FALSE,FALSE,NA,http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Naomi_Campbell,http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/Naomi_Campbell

column45: 'Modern Dog' - Fall 2010","Cooking, Jetskiing, Running, Scuba Diving, Swimming, Exercising","Niki's full name is Nicole Renee Taylor. She was raised in Fort Lauderdale and as a child she dreamed of becoming a model. Her dream came true at age 13 when she was accepted onto the books of a Florida agency, going on to win a Fresh Faces contest in New York. Her prize was a $500,000 modelling contract. By the age of 16, she was a millionaire and president of her own company, Niki, Inc. At one point, however, Niki had planned to become a marine biologist (she has a tattoo of a dolphin on her ankle, as well as others such as a sun on her foot). Despite her rocketing modelling career, Niki continued with her education. She went on to study special effects for film and TV after she graduated from high school, and she also took singing lessons and dance classes. In 1991, Niki was named as one of People magazine's '50 Most Beautiful People' and has released her own calendar for several years. She appeared in the 1997, 1998 & 1999 Sports Illustrated Swimsuit Edition. She was the youngest model to sign a major cosmetics contract with L'Oreal for Cover Girl. In July 1995, her younger sister Krissy (another promising model) sadly died from asthma complications. Niki also has an older sister called Joelle. Niki's official web-site can be found here: www.nikitaylorinc.com. She appeared in the 'Sports Illustrated knockouts five decades og swimsuit photography' book. Niki appears in Keith Urban's ""Somebody Like You"" music video - Official Website: www.nikitaylor.com",B,FALSE,FALSE,NA,http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niki_Taylor,http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/Niki_Taylor

column12: 'Viva Magazine' - February 2006",,"At the age of 17, Rachel was persuaded by her aunt to try modelling and she travelled to New York where she was signed by the Ford agency. She later landed the Cover Girl cosmetics contract and became the spokesperson for the company. Rachel has appeared in a fitness video for Sports Illustrated and has produced her own fitness video with her trainer, Todd Person, as well as starring in a VH-1 exercise show called 'Body'. There has also been a TV documentary of her life entitled 'Rachel Hunter - Cover Girl'. Rachel is very famous in her native New Zealand and when one magazine put her face on the cover, sales of that issue increased by 10,000. - Rachel was in ""Stacy's Mom"" music video by Fountains of Wayne. - She appeared in 'Sports Illustrated Swimsuit' in 1989, 1990, 1991, 1993, 1994, 1995 & 2004. - She has a tattoo on her tummy and lower back. - Her Official Web Site: www.rachelhunter.com",C,FALSE,TRUE,A,http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rachel_Hunter,http://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/Rachel_Hunter
